        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 11:13PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 1113 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hanover, or 14 miles northwest of Welch, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Davy, Hanover, R.d. Bailey Lake, Gilbert Creek, Bradshaw, Elbert,
Ghent, Keystone, Coalwood, Hurley, Rhodell, Avondale, Wolf Pen,
Welch, Josephine, Jenkinjones, Herndon, Iaeger, Kimball, and Gary.

This includes West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 28 and 29.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
